# MRJC Vlogs — Next.js Starter

This repository is a ready-to-run **Next.js (App Router)** starter for **MRJC Vlogs** with Tailwind CSS and Framer Motion page transitions (swipe left/right + zoom).

## What's included
- Next.js App Router structure (pages: Home, Vlogs, Gallery, Contact)
- Tailwind CSS setup
- Framer Motion page transitions and element animations
- Social links (YouTube, TikTok, Facebook)
- Optional automatic YouTube latest-uploads embed (requires API key + channel ID)
- README + Vercel one-click instructions

---

## Local setup

1. Install dependencies
```bash
npm install
```

2. Run dev server
```bash
npm run dev
# open http://localhost:3000
```

## YouTube automatic embeds (optional)

To show the **latest uploads** automatically on the Vlogs page, set the following environment variables locally or in your deployment platform (Vercel):

- `YOUTUBE_API_KEY` — your Google API key with YouTube Data API v3 enabled
- `YOUTUBE_CHANNEL_ID` — your channel ID (not the handle). Example: `UC_x5XG1OV2P6uZZ5FSM9Ttw`

If those variables are set, the site will fetch the latest videos server-side and embed them. If they are not set, a fallback static embed + subscribe link will be shown.

### How to get your Channel ID
1. Go to your channel page on YouTube. 
2. Click `Customize Channel` -> `Basic info`, the Channel ID will be displayed. (If you have a handle, you may need to look under advanced settings or use a lookup tool.)

## Vercel one-click deploy

You can deploy to Vercel quickly. Create a new Vercel project and connect your GitHub repo, then add the environment variables `YOUTUBE_API_KEY` and `YOUTUBE_CHANNEL_ID` if you want automatic embeds.

A sample Vercel button (use in a GitHub README):

```md
[![Deploy to Vercel](https://vercel.com/button)](https://vercel.com/new/git/import?repository-url=https://github.com/USERNAME/REPO_NAME)
```

When deploying, configure the environment variables in the Vercel dashboard.

